    "John Trapp": "That he might not reign. ] He deposed him; to show that he had now the disposal of the kingdom. Or, Because he reigned, sc., without his good leave and liking.\nVer.\n33. The stain of it was like iron mould, which nothing can fetch out. His posterity also, yea, and the generality of the people, persisting in Manasseh\u2019s sins, were justly punishable for the same. The Corinthians were accessory to the sin of the incestuous person, because they bewailed it not; {#1Co 5:2} and shall not we of this age smart for those bloody Marian days, if we lament not, and so disclaim them?\nVer.\n33. That he might not reign.] He deposed him; to show that he had now the disposal of the kingdom. Or, Because he reigned, sc., without his good leave and liking.\nVer."
