  "5": {
    "James D. Nogalski, James W Knox": "715",
    "John Trapp": "And he put down the idolatrous priests. ] Heb., Chemarims, Baal\u2019s chimney-chaplains, { see #Zep 1:14 , with the note there } black sooty fellows, like those greasy mass priests, or abbey lubbers, amongst the Papists. And to the planets. ] Or, Influences: a radice Nazal fluxit.\nVer.\n5. And he put down the idolatrous priests.] Heb., [v_Zep_1_14] Chemarims, Baal\u2019s chimney-chaplains, {see #Zep 1:14, with the note there} black sooty fellows, like those greasy mass priests, or abbey lubbers, amongst the Papists. And to the planets.] Or, Influences: a radice Nazal fluxit.\nVer.\n5. Ahaz was \u03b5\u03b9\u03b4\u03c9\u03bb\u03bf\u03bc\u03b1\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2. And the altars which Manasseh had made.] These, after his repentance, he cast out of the city, {#2Ch 33:15} but not so thoroughly abolished; hence they became snares to his successors. And brake them down from thence.] Or, Ran from thence; quam citissime potuit discedens illinc, { a} he got out of those loathsome places as soon as he could. Into the brook Kidron, ] i.e., The town ditch. {a} Vatab.\nVer.\n5. And with all his might.] Heb., With his utmost vehemency, strength, and diligence; he did all that he could do.\nVer.\n5. Moreover four thousand were porters. ] Quos barbare vocant Sacristas. And four thousand praised the Lord. ] Whereof some were teachers, { #1Ch 25:7 } and some scholars. Which I made, ] i.e., Invented, { #Am 6:6 } and appointed to be used in the temple by God\u2019s commandment. { #1Ch 29 1Ch 25 }\nVer.\n5. Moreover four thousand were porters.] Quos barbare vocant Sacristas. And four thousand praised the Lord.] Whereof some were teachers, {#1Ch 25:7} and some scholars. [v_Amo_6_6] Which I made, ] i.e., Invented, {#Am 6:6} and appointed to be used in the temple by God\u2019s commandment. {#1Ch 29 1Ch 25}\nVer."
  },
